ce:section.ce:para:
The main purpose of preparing a fluorescence sensor is detecting analytes in real samples with minimal pretreatment. To investigate the application of the suggested method in real samples, standard recovery experiments were performed in human plasma samples (Table 1
                        ). A 5% aliquot of pretreated plasma samples was prepared and reacted for 1 h, and its ﬂuorescence intensity was measured. Recovery of the proposed method was obtained as 95%–105% demonstrating that, it was feasible to determine Clonazepam in plasma samples. Table 2
                         summarizes the results obtained by analyzing 1 mg of Clonazepam pharmaceutical tablet samples by this method, all of which were satisfactory with average Clonazepam recoveries of 95%–105%. In addition, experimental process was completed very fast showing that, this method is able to quickly determine Clonazepam in real samples.
